16:42.000 --> 16:47.000
Especially if it is the first two categories.

16:48.000 --> 17:00.000
The last thing to note is that data registration is a rather problematic occupation.

17:00.000 --> 17:06.000
Because a person, especially if we talk about the first two cases,

17:06.000 --> 17:11.000
cannot sit and record what he sees.

17:12.000 --> 17:20.000
That is, he must record the data registration after some time.

17:20.000 --> 17:25.000
This can also lead to some distortions.

17:25.000 --> 17:33.000
Something is lost in memory, something has already been seen by someone else through the prism of time.

17:33.000 --> 17:36.000
Of course, there are methods that allow this to be avoided.

17:36.000 --> 17:43.000
One of them is the recommendation to register data as soon as possible.

17:43.000 --> 17:46.000
People took a break, quickly recorded something.

17:46.000 --> 17:50.000
At the end of the working day, in no case can it be postponed.

17:50.000 --> 17:53.000
Nevertheless, such a problem exists.

17:54.000 --> 18:06.000
In order to reduce the disadvantages, there are approaches to their minimization.

18:06.000 --> 18:20.000
Despite the cost of this method, the first thing to ask for is to include two or three researchers in the observation.

18:20.000 --> 18:28.000
The first is to duplicate the live researcher with a video camera.

18:28.000 --> 18:39.000
Then, to make a kind of average and reduce the prism of perception of each individual person.

18:39.000 --> 18:46.000
But you can go the other way, as you have indicated in the workbook.

